{
  "stem": "1061.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I adored it, because we were very much in tune with our surroundings.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did not live a-- a-- a ghetto-ized type of existence.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We mingled with the Christians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We attended their Christmas dinners and-- and went to look at their Christmas trees.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they would come for Passovers to our home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we just felt ourselves part of the community, even though we were Jewish and participated in the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But not-- my parents were only religious to an extent that, you know, they attended synagogue and such.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were not-- we were not kosher, you see.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were not religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "However, they had a very strong Jewish identity.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this is how my mother was so involved with the Zionist movement, because that was their way of-- of reaffirming what they considered themselves to be.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in fact, I went after my regular school-- excuse me-- I went to a Hebrew afternoon school, which was a secular school, you see, to learn the language and to study the poems of [INAUDIBLE] and such.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was very interesting because it was just one more language to learn.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and of course, that ended with the war, as my education, my formal Polish education, ended because the Jewish children were not allowed to participate in schools.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, there's always a way to manage, otherwise.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I have a frog in my throat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anyhow, what happened is because my oldest sister had all of the books at home, and we children were really not allowed in the streets for the reason that the Germans who-- the gestapo were always around with dogs.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it was just absolute, total terror for a child to be outside and see these-- these marching-- you know, the German-- the gestapo with the dogs, they sort of had a-- they-- they had a certain posture.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And just looking at it was frightening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, we used to go swimming in the [INAUDIBLE], but not during the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We couldn't travel on trains, that was forbidden.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Going to Polish school was out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So what remained wasn't killing time, was really using the resources that were available.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And frankly, I think I had my-- the-- the underlying foundation for my later higher education is really based on what I have acquired during those days, those two years locked up in a house.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, it kept us very stimulated, intellectually.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And probably away from the fear and the horror, and all the other things that were going out-- on outside.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it is sort of a difficult question because, you understand, I was very young.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was not in any way persecuted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were well accepted in town, even though toward the end of the '30s there were boycotts of Jewish stores.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We did not own stores.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, my father was not a storekeeper.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see, my grandmother, who I refer to my mother's mother, her name was Sarah Tenenblum, lived about 20 miles away from us in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she and-- had two daughters that weren't yet married, my Aunt Regina, after whom I am-- I have a name, and my-- and Anjia owned a printing shop.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First of all, we're talking about my being eight or nine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would go, of course be taken into the printing shop.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was allowed to go to the-- where the facility, the operation of the-- of the-- of the painting was taking place.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was allowed to-- to touch the machinery because the gentleman who worked in the back knew me, and of course they-- they wanted to impress me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then on the way home-- before I would go home, I would collect a bag of-- they would collect it for me, you know, when they would print, let's say, posters.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they would cut them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all of the thing-- the paper strips that would fall off would be put in a bag.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then if they did ledgers, and they puncture these round holes, which made a bag of confetti.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Well of course, I was-- I was absolutely it with a capital I when I came back home.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I had these bags of this wonderful stuff.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And of course, I think I was injected with printer's ink because I'm a very-- I'm an avid reader, and I have always adored reading.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I think this is where it really came from.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I-- I really-- this is it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[DRINKS] Grandmother's-- my grandmother herself, though she was very religious, was very well educated for a woman of her time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She spoke French fluently, and she came from a very fine family.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
